verbose_text: The levels of PpIX fluorescence produced by AP2-18 as well as the PDT effects (as assessed by the lactate dehydrogenase and neutral red assays) produced within each cell type following subsequent irradiation have therefore been compared against the established PpIX precursors ALA and MAL administered either alone, or in combination with, the most effective known iron chelating agent for this purpose, CP94.
